    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-10-15T06:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1968-10-15T06:30:00-05:00" n="71"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d71">
                <head>71. Information Memorandum From the President’s Special Assistant (<persName
                        corresp="#p_RWW1" type="from">Rostow</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_JLB1" type="to">Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d71fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_JLB1"
                            >Johnson</persName> Library, National Security File, Country File,
                        Vietnam, 9/30-10/22/68, Memos to the President/Bombing Halt Decision, Vol. I
                        [3 of 3]. Secret; <gloss target="#t_HARVAN1">HARVAN</gloss>/Double Plus. The
                        notation “ps” on the memorandum indicates that the President saw it.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1968-10-15T07:30:00-04:00">October 15, 1968, 7:30 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Mr. President:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_VCR1">Cy Vance</persName> called from Paris to report the
                    following:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_XTC1">Thuy</persName> called him personally on the
                    telephone—the first time he has ever done this. He asked: Are you ready for a
                    meeting this morning? (Paris time.) <persName corresp="#p_VCR1">Cy</persName>
                    said no. <persName corresp="#p_XTC1">Thuy</persName> then asked, could you be
                    ready for a meeting at 3:00 p.m.? (Paris time.) <persName corresp="#p_VCR1"
                        >Cy</persName> said no. <persName corresp="#p_VCR1">Cy</persName> then said
                    he would be willing to set up a meeting, tentatively, for 9:00 p.m. (Paris time;
                    4:00 <pb facs="0233" n="199" xml:id="pg_199"/> p.m. our time). He did so on the
                    assumption that we would then have the <gloss target="#t_TCC1">TCC</gloss>
                    replies and an execute order from us in hand on his instructions, which are now
                    pre-positioned in Paris for a go ahead.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_VCR1">Cy</persName> does not know what <persName
                        corresp="#p_XTC1">Thuy</persName> has in mind. He and <persName
                        corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName> believe that <persName
                        corresp="#p_XTC1">Thuy</persName> has the authority to agree on <gloss
                        target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> participation and express “understanding” on
                    the <gloss target="#t_DMZ1">DMZ</gloss> and the cities. He does not know how
                    they will make out on reconnaissance, but is implicitly optimistic.</p>
                <p>(<persName corresp="#p_HPC1">Habib</persName>, on the other hand, rather doubts
                    that <persName corresp="#p_XTC1">Thuy</persName> will have the authority to give
                    a final assent without a check with Hanoi. In fact, <persName corresp="#p_HPC1"
                        >Habib</persName>’s theory is Tho is going back to Hanoi to help explain to
                    and persuade his colleagues if we should come through.)</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_VCR1">Vance</persName> is very much worried about a leak
                    in the wake of our informing the <gloss target="#t_TCC1">TCC</gloss>’s.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_VCR1">Vance</persName> would like to be able to tell
                        <persName corresp="#p_XTC1">Thuy</persName>—if he agrees on the <gloss
                        target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss>, understands on the <gloss target="#t_DMZ1"
                        >DMZ</gloss>, cities and <gloss target="#t_recce1">recce</gloss>—that we
                    would stop the bombing tomorrow.</p>
                <p>Attached is a possible scenario which <persName corresp="#p_GRN1">Bob
                        Ginsburgh</persName> and I have worked out this morning, made up before
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR1">Cy Vance</persName>’s telephone call, but
                    roughly consistent with it.</p>
                <p>This scenario is based on the notion that we would announce tonight that the
                    bombing will cease tomorrow.</p>
                <p>You should know that Bus Wheeler wants 24 hours for two reasons: <list>
                        <item>—To make sure that everyone gets the word and there are no
                            mistakes;</item>
                        <item>—To try to get out of North Vietnam (south of the 20th parallel)
                            certain agents we have put in there, to whom we owe something.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>As between waiting 24 hours and announcing the “bombing has stopped” and saying
                    the “bombing will stop tomorrow,” I favor the latter to minimize the possibility
                    of leaks.</p>
                <p>All of this is, of course, based on the assumption that <persName
                        corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_VCR1"
                        >Vance</persName> are right; that is, <persName corresp="#p_XTC1"
                        >Thuy</persName> has positive pre-positioned instructions on all our points.
                    There are ample opportunities in this scenario for a holdup—or worse.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Walt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>P.S. We have no <gloss target="#t_TCC1">TCC</gloss> responses yet but expect
                        them very soon.<note n="2" xml:id="d71fn2">
                            <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">Rostow</persName> added the following
                            handwritten note: “Correction: <persName corresp="#p_TK1"
                                >Thanom</persName> now aboard. W.”</note>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
                <pb facs="0234" n="200" xml:id="pg_200"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head>Attachment<note n="3" xml:id="d71fn3">This attachment was handwritten by
                                <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">Rostow</persName>.</note>
                    </head>
                    <p rend="center">Possible Sequence of Events</p>
                    <table cols="4" rows="13">
                        <row role="label">
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Saigon</cell>
                            <cell>Paris</cell>
                            <cell>EDT Washington</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>1. <gloss target="#t_DRV1">DRV</gloss> agrees to <gloss
                                    target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> participation.</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 0400</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 2100</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 1600</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>2. Issue orders to stop bombing. (16 EDT 1700)</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 0500</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 2200</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 1700</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>3. Tell Paris to inform <gloss target="#t_DRV1">DRV</gloss> of
                                time.</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 0500</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 2200</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 1700</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>4. Inform Marcos.</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 0500</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 2200</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 1700</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>5. Inform <gloss target="#t_TCC1">TCC</gloss>s of timing.</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 0500</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 2200</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 1700</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>6. Brief candidates.</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 0600</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 2300</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 1800</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>7. Brief leadership.</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 0700</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 2400</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 1900</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>8. Joint announcement.</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 0800</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 0100</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 2000</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>9. Presidential statement.</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 0800+</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 0100+</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 2000+</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>10. Backgrounder.</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 0900</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 0200</cell>
                            <cell role="num">15 2100</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>11. Bombing stops.</cell>
                            <cell role="num">17 0500</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 2200</cell>
                            <cell role="num">16 1700</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>12. Paris meetings—<gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss>
                                included.</cell>
                            <cell role="num">17 1700</cell>
                            <cell role="num">17 1000</cell>
                            <cell role="num">17 0500</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
